 letters, rendered somewhat crude and deep due to the coarse stone. Sigma is four-bar with slightly open upper and lower strokes; omega is large, rounded and open with short tails; alpha has straight bar; epsilon has shorter middle bar; nu has three full length strokes, first and last vertical; mu has vertical first and last, but shorter middle strokes descending only half-way; omicron is full-size; rho has fairly large rounded, closed eye.",[41,48],{"type":42,"l":43,"from":44,"to":45,"h":46,"unit":47,"atLeast":46,"atMost":46},"letterHeight","Line 1-3","line1","line3","100","mm",{"type":49,"l":50,"from":44,"to":51,"unit":47},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":53,"notBefore":54,"notAfter":55,"evidence":56},"Later 4th or 3rd century BCE on the basis of the letter forms",-350,-201,"lettering",[58,63],{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"region":62},"Enna","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462236","Sicilia",{"_":59,"type":64,"ref":65,"region":62},"modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2524819",[67],[68,69],37.5655,14.27433,[71,72],37.569808,14.286365,"Sicily","",{"_":76,"mainLang":77,"languages":78},"Ancient Greek","grc",[76],"644997",{"n":81,"url":82,"height":83,"width":84,"desc":85,"surfaceType":86},"screen","ISic001491_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front",[88],{"atLeast":89,"atMost":89},100,[91,91,92,93,93,94,95,96,97],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Dubois, 1989, IGDS1","Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-","Vollgraff, 1951, Inhumation en terre sacrée dans l'antiquité grecque (à propos d'une inscription d'Argos)","Manganaro, 1965, Ricerche di antichità e di epigrafia siceliote","Masson, 1986, Vocabulaire grec et épigraphie: ἀρχός \"chef, archonte\"","Manganaro, 2003, Demetra degli Ennaioi",[99,99,100,101,101,102,103,104,105],"F2GG87EQ","RWXNUFEX","4MCP2PVV","36MK85X6","RGT